HiShare — licensing overview
============================

HiShare is the modernized edition of BeShare 3.04 by Jeremy Friesner.
Different parts of this source tree are covered by different licenses:

1. BeShare / HiShare application code
   (source/hishare/*, excluding the santa/ subdirectory)

   The original BeShare code was placed in the public domain by its author,
   Jeremy Friesner (1999-2012). The HiShare modernization (2026, atomozero)
   is likewise released into the public domain: do with it what you want.

2. MUSCLE networking library
   (source/muscle/)

   Copyright Meyer Sound Laboratories Inc., distributed under its own
   BSD-style license. See source/muscle/LICENSE.

3. Santa's Gift Bag GUI classes — ColumnListView, BetterScrollView, etc.
   (source/hishare/santa/)

   Copyright Brian Tietz, distributed under its own license, which allows
   free use in freeware and cheap shareware and requires keeping its
   documentation and license alongside the code, with modifications clearly
   marked. See source/hishare/santa/License. HiShare is free software, so
   its use here is within those terms; the HiShare modifications to these
   classes (Haiku theme-awareness, etc.) are marked in the sources.

4. zlib
   (source/muscle/zlib/zlib/)

   Copyright Jean-loup Gailly and Mark Adler, zlib license.

Note on source/hishare/BeShareSSLKeys.h: the PEM key pair embedded there is
NOT a secret. It is a well-known, shared key that ships inside every binary
and provides opportunistic transport encryption only (protection against
passive eavesdropping), not authentication. See the comments in that file,
including how to regenerate the pair.
